You are implementing Tasks 5-8: Backend rewrite with Claude Agent SDK V2 Session API

## Context

This is a web chat application for a "Mindful Consumption Guide" agent. The base code is from the `simple-chatapp` demo in the Claude Agent SDK demos repo. We need to:
1. Add new types for persona/config
2. Rewrite ai-client.ts to use the V2 Session API (not the old query() approach)
3. Add config endpoint and file upload to server.ts
4. Update session.ts for persona injection

The project is at: /Users/glnelson/dev/s26_spike/s26_3_31_class_and_guide

A `skill-loader.ts` has already been created at `server/skill-loader.ts` that exports:
- `loadSkills(skillsDir: string): SkillMeta[]`
- `buildSystemPrompt(skills: SkillMeta[]): string`
- `SkillMeta` interface: `{ name: string; description: string; content: string }`

An `agent-config.json` exists at the project root with shape:
```json
{
  "name": "Mindful Consumption Guide",
  "description": "...",
  "welcome_message": "...",
  "accent_color": "#4A7C59",
  "persona_fields": [{ "key": "name", "label": "Name", "type": "text", "required": false, "placeholder": "..." }, ...]
}
```

## Task 5: Add types to server/types.ts

The current types.ts has: WSClient, Chat, ChatMessage, WSChatMessage, WSSubscribeMessage, IncomingWSMessage.

Add these new types:

```typescript
export interface PersonaField {
  key: string;
  label: string;
  type: "text" | "number" | "textarea";
  required: boolean;
  placeholder?: string;
}

export interface AgentConfig {
  name: string;
  description: string;
  welcome_message: string;
  accent_color: string;
  persona_fields: PersonaField[];
}

export interface PersonaData {
  [key: string]: string | number | undefined;
}

export interface UploadedFile {
  originalName: string;
  storedPath: string;
  uploadedAt: string;
}
```

Also update WSChatMessage to optionally include persona:
```typescript
export interface WSChatMessage {
  type: "chat";
  content: string;
  chatId: string;
  persona?: PersonaData;
}
```

## Task 6: Rewrite ai-client.ts with V2 Session API

Replace the current query()-based approach with the V2 Session API. The V2 API uses:

```typescript
import {
  unstable_v2_createSession,
  unstable_v2_resumeSession,
} from "@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk";
```

Key V2 patterns:
